title: For Sale/Trade:  Mini - 14 GB (Government Barrel) Liberty model
postcontent:
Ruger Mini 14 GB Model Series 180 made in 1976 and is marked "Made in the 200th year of American Liberty.

The GB stands for government barrel and is the only factory gun to come with a flash hider and bayonet lug. A GB is easily distinguished by the front sight which is set back from the muzzle as opposed to incorporated at the muzzle end. The flash hider is threaded onto the barrel rather than slid over the muzzle and pinned. The 180 series GB is unique because it has a thinner and sleeker stock and fore end. It also has a roller cam bolt that is much smoother when cycling than the later models and has never failed to eject or feed. 

This gun is in 95% condition and shows some handling wear to the butt plate, rear sight and stock. The barrel and action are clean and in great shape. 

This gun has a long history in Law Enforcement as it began life as a California Department Of Corrections rifle until it was finally sold off. It was then carried as a patrol rifle in a small Kansas Town. 

This is not only a beautiful example of the Mini 14 but is an excellent shooter. I carried this gun as a duty weapon and can make consistent head shots with iron sights at 100 yards. The gun likes the Winchester 55grain FMJ and 55 grain SP

The gun comes with 5 and 20 round magazines plus 100 rounds of ammo.

title: For Sale/Trade:  RARE AK47 in .223 caliber PSO-1 rechargeable night scope
location: 570-20 Miles North of Allentown, Southeastern, PA, Pennsylvania
postcontent:
I have a Romanian SAR 3 AK-47 in .223 caliber chambering w/ 4 mags, factory scope rail and a vietnam era PSO-1 night scope wth all charging accesories.Have factory target sighting used for sighting the scope in.These AK's are known as the "Mini-Dragonov" as it has the dragonov sniper scope and dragonov factory side rail scope mount, made to attach and detach in 30 seconds for quick set-up and take down.

The PSO-1 was specifically designed for the SVD as a telescopic sight for military designated marksman activities. The current version of the sight is the PSO-1M2. This telescopic sight is different from the original PSO-1 only in that it lacks the now obsolete Infra-Red detector. The metal body of the PSO-1 is made from a magnesium alloy. The PSO-1 features a battery powered red illuminated reticle with light provided by a simple diode bulb. It features professionally ground, fully multi-coated optical elements, a baked enamel finish for scratch protection, and an attached, quick-deployable, extendable sunshade. The scope body is sealed and filled with nitrogen, which prevents fogging of optics and was designed to function within a -50 °C to 50 °C temperature range. Considered the higher end of Soviet military side mount telescopic sights, the quality of the PSO-1 is higher than most other PSO-style telescopic sights. The PSO-1 is the most modern of military tactical scopes with lower power fixed magnification Has the 2" rubber scope eyepiece for comfortability in long sittings, also has a 2 1/2" extendable sunshade for daytime use

These AK's go for $200-$300 more than the 7.62's all day, that's if you can find it in this caliber, the scopes are rare as well and are worth $350-$400 in good condition. All markings are in russian all over scope however charger has been changed to U.S type socket. 
 The AK's in great shape, furniture is in good shape no rust, pitting, or marks that would cause this weapon to lose value and has factory target sheet used to sight in scope and test gun at the factory.as well as all the accesories before mentioned.

willing to trade for AR's, Ruger, Glock 17 pistols, Also Gold coins

title: For Sale:  KIMBER SIS Custom/RL 45 ACP
postcontent:
This is the full size Kimber 45 in the SIS configuration with the built-in tactical rail. I've hung the little Crimson Trace RailMaster laser on it for fun, but I'll keep it if you're not thrilled with it.

Like all SIS's this one is made of stainless steel covered with Kimber's KimPro finish. The slide is machined in the SIS style with a flat top and SIS cocking serrations.  It has the SIS special night sights (with cocking shoulder) so you can always see your gun sights.  The railed frame is checkered, and it has an ambidextrous safety. The gun will come with the Kimber case and two stainless steel 8 rnd magazines (a Kimber KimPro Tac-Mag and a Mec-Gar tactical mag).

This SIS has everything the Kimber Warrior configuration has (except lanyard loop and synthetic grips) and more, being stainless steel.  In fact, if you compare important features, you'd have to go up to Kimber's Gold Combat RL before you beat this SIS.  Add a magwell and grips to this one and you're there.

This gun functions flawlessly, but it is not as pretty as a brand new one. The KimPro finish has taken a couple of scratches (not through to the stainless steel, and with a thin coat of oil, they are almost invisible) and the fancy SIS wood grips are a little beat up. It is a great shooter, but not necessarily one for your pristine SIS collection.

The extra weight of the rail makes this a very easy to steady weapon, so the red laser dot stays where you put it [this in contrast to my little Ultra Carry whose laser dot dances all over the target].  The more I write about this gun, the less I want to sell it, but this is a good time to build up some cash.  If you prefer, I will keep the laser and sell the SIS for $1100.

If this ad is up, the gun is available. No trades thanks, and please let's not start negotiating the price until you see the gun.
